<span id="Description"></span>
==Beschreibung==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The [[Image:Cables_DeactivateAttachment.svg|24px]] [[Cables_DeactivateAttachment|Deactivate Attachment]] disables current attachment of an object. The '''Map Mode''' property of an object is set to {{Value|Deactivated}}, other attachment properties remain untouched.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
This is useful when the attachment is not needed temporary. Deactivated '''Map Mode''' enables precise object movement e.g. with [[Std_TransformManip|TransformManip]] tool. After placement correction the [[Cables_AttachInPlace|AttachInPlace]] tool can be used to apply corrected '''Attachment Offset''' property.
</div>

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Anwendung==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Select one or more objects in the [[3D_View|3D View]] or [[Tree_View|Tree View]] holding the {{KEY|CTRL}} key.
# [[Cables_DeactivateAttachment|Deactivate Attachment]] of all selected objects by one of these methods:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Cables_DeactivateAttachment.svg|16px]] [[Cables_DeactivateAttachment|DeactivateAttachment]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Cable Support → [[Image:Cables_DeactivateAttachment.svg|16px]] Deactivate Attachment}} option from the menu.
#* Right-click in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]] or the [[3D_View|3D View]] and select the {{MenuCommand|Cable Support → [[Image:Cables_DeactivateAttachment.svg|16px]] Deactivate Attachment}} option from the context menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|X}} then {{KEY|D}}.
</div>

<span id="Notes"></span>
==Hinweise==

Auswahl von Elementen in der [[3D_View/de|3D-Ansicht]] wird als Auswahl ganzer Objekte behandelt.


